            "id": "s_l5_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Living Objects 🤖",
            "content": "Objects can hold more than just data.\n\nThey can hold **Functions** too!\n\nWhen a function is a property of an object, it's called a **Method**."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l5_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l5_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "What is a Method?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "A special variable",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "A function on an object",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "Methods are functions attached to objects."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l5_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Example 🐕",
            "content": "Let's make a dog object that can bark.",
            "codeSnippet": "let dog = {\n  name: 'Rex',\n  bark: function() {\n    console.log('Woof!');\n  }\n};\n\ndog.bark(); // Woof!",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l5_4",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Shorthand ✨",
            "content": "In modern JS, you can skip the `: function` part.",
            "codeSnippet": "let cat = {\n  meow() {\n    console.log('Meow!');\n  }\n};\n\ncat.meow();",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
